<br>
Go to start - run - notepad, and type your user/pass there make sure your keyboard buttons havent been acting up (since you cant see your pwd the ***'s)<br>
<br>
The zip code on your account is the zip code tied to the credit card your account is billed to.  might check if its an old card, use that code.<br>
<br>
I would look around on station.com for ways to have your password reset via the registered email address on the account, there usually is a way to do this.<br>
<br>
Unfortunately if someone were to receive your password they could change it with minimal problems, as well as changing your account details. does anyone else know your password? or is it like your RL name or something easy to figure out?  are you on a local network where people could sniff / decode packets from your box?  usually peoples accounts are hacked because they give out the password.  and its not impossible to load a virus type program on your machine that records keyboard keystrokes.  do other EQ players have access to your PC? (i.e. do you play in a public *game room)<br>
<br>
